# App drawer (slide-in panel + scrim)

**Vocabulary:** In Guardian, **drawer** means the app-wide trailing ``AppDrawer`` (scrim + slide-in panel). **Sidebar** means the main navigation rail in ``RootView`` — not ``AppDrawer``.

When adding or changing an **app-wide trailing drawer**:

- **Must** use the central template: ``AppDrawer`` + ``View/withAppDrawer()`` (see ``Sources/GuardianHQ/General/Utilities/Templates/AppDrawer.swift``). Do not invent a parallel scrim + slide-in host or local `ZStack` scrims + `transition(.move(edge: .trailing))` for app-wide trailing drawers.
- Inject ``@EnvironmentObject private var appDrawer: AppDrawer`` and call ``present(title:preferredWidth:scrimTapDismisses:animation:content:)`` / ``dismiss()``.
- Use ``title: nil`` when the content view already includes a full custom header (e.g. segmented control in the header). Use a non-nil ``title`` when the shared ``AppDrawerChrome`` (title + close) should wrap the body.
- Dismiss overlays when leaving a screen if needed (e.g. ``onDisappear``); tab changes already call ``dismiss()`` from ``RootView``.
- Window stacking: see ``GuardianLayoutPatterns`` — ``withAppDrawer()`` wraps ``RootView``; ``withGuardianConfirmOverlayHost()`` stacks on that; ``withOperatorPromptPersistentToasts()`` then ``withToasts()`` (ephemeral) stack outward.
- Reference: **Theme** panel → **App drawer** section (scrim swatches, ``AppDrawerChrome`` preview, live sample ``present``).
